    {
      "id": "b4301c42c85a4a6b5a519ad1acdf00d883fbf3ae",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-08 19:18:44.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review-1\n\n(1 comment)\n\nAmir, Dmitry, can you please review.\n\nI'm not wholly against this change, because I don't think many sites are using lnet.conf, but there needs to be some consideration given for the upgrade case in the lustre.spec to handle any existing /etc/sysconfig/lnet.conf file.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "58a8d721e6d66a64694ce5ee66227ec9d6ad4ad2",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-08 19:19:27.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "34f16b5024d5809aafe80780e4ca88c4fe65c731",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 308,
        "name": "Amir Shehata",
        "email": "ashehata@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "ashehata"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-08 19:21:21.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: -Code-Review\n\n(1 comment)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "c33ffa3bd1837d20572bbb2da4b378924dc95915",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 564,
        "name": "Giuseppe Di Natale",
        "email": "dinatale2@llnl.gov",
        "username": "dinatale2"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-08 20:45:45.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> (1 comment)\n > \n > Amir, Dmitry, can you please review.\n > \n > I'm not wholly against this change, because I don't think many\n > sites are using lnet.conf, but there needs to be some consideration\n > given for the upgrade case in the lustre.spec to handle any\n > existing /etc/sysconfig/lnet.conf file.\n\nFrom my understanding, /etc/sysconfig is for configuration files that are directly importable in scripts. All other configuration formats should be in /etc with a suitable name.\n\nAre you aware of sites using lnetctl? According to the lustre spec file, DLC is not built by default. I figured this may be a low risk move to get the config file both where it should be and provide a sample. Am I wrong on that?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "04c61cb143060aac28c7462825e9df013b5888ee",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-09 03:04:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3: Code-Review+1\n\nAmir, you would know better about the use of lnetctl and /etc/sysconfig/lnet.conf. \n\nIf you don't think that there are many users then I'd be Ok with a simple move from the existing location (if any) to the new location, and we can skip the downgrade (which is yet a smaller fraction of the already small number of users).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
    {
      "id": "9d4c333d130e0b10b78db4c4994d35c2b60faf3c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-05-09 17:01:08.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nAnother option might be to ask on lustre-discuss to see if there are any users there.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 3
    },
